  "text": "Daugman's Rubber Sheet Model: Normalization process involves unwrapping the iris and converting it into its polar equivalent. It is done using Daugman's Rubber sheet model [CITATION_1] and is shown in figure. For every pixel in the iris, an equivalent position is found out on polar axes. The process comprises of two resolutions: Radial resolution, which is the number of data points in the radial direction and Angular resolution, which is the number of radial lines generated around iris region. Using the following equation, the iris region is transformed to a 2D array with horizontal dimensions of angular resolution and vertical dimension of radial resolution. ",
